      "raw_text": "negotiations with the railroads west\nof the Mississippi.\n\n\nThe first move in this regard is\nseen in the manner in which the\nNorthern Pacific is dealing with the\ncommittee representing the trainmen\nof that line. Up to the present time\nthere have been only two conferences,\nbut the trainmen have received in\nformation that the company is not in\nclined to meet their demands on the\ndouble heading proposition.\n\n\n1t is said to amount to fiat re-\nfusal, although it is not couched in\nthose terms. No further conferences\nhave been arranged and officers of\ntrainmen's unions have returned to\nChicago."
